# LLM Wiki Structure

- Treat `raw/` as the immutable source layer.
- Keep original source documents in `raw/articles/` and attachments in `raw/assets/`.
- Store one derived note per source in `wiki/source-notes/`.
- Put durable topic pages in `wiki/entities/`, `wiki/concepts/`, or `wiki/synthesis/`.
- Do not silently convert raw files into wiki pages. Create a derived page instead.
- Update `wiki/index.md` when adding a durable wiki page.
- Keep `logs/log.md` append-only for ingests, lint passes, and major analyses.
